rdgGrp.n: ['his', 'literary pursuits differed wholly from those which had occupied me. he came to the university with the design of making himself complete master of the oriental languages, as thus he', 'should']

['for the plan of life he had marked out for himself. resolved to pursue no inglorious career, he turned his eyes toward the east, as affording scope for his spirit of enterprise.', 'the persian, arabic, and sanscrit languages', 'engaged']
['and i was easily induced to enter on the same studies.']
